e for the class of\nnoetherian Leavitt path algebras: if $L_{\\mathbb C}(E)$ and $L_{\\mathbb C}(F)$\nare noetherian Leavitt path algebras, then $L_{\\mathbb C}(E)\\cong L_{\\mathbb\nC}(F)$ as rings implies $C^*(E)\\cong C^*(F)$ as $^\\ast$-algebras.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Nov 2013 14:24:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-11-06"}
